CIMB, Axiata, Maxis, Maybank, MMC, RHB: Malaysia Equity Preview

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-06-01T00:05:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/cimb-axiata-maxis-maybank-mmc-rhb-malaysia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in  Malaysia  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index rose 1 percent to
1,558.29.  Banks:  CIMB Group Holdings Bhd. (CIMB)   and  Malayan
Banking Bhd. (MAY)   won separate central bank approval to
begin competing merger talks with  RHB Capital Bhd. (RHBC)  ,
according to company statements. CIMB gained 1.3 percent to 8.37
ringgit, Malayan Banking, or Maybank, added 0.8 percent to 8.91
ringgit and RHB slid 0.7 percent to 9.22 ringgit.        Axiata Group Bhd. (AXIATA)  : The Malaysian mobile-phone
operator said first-quarter net income fell 40 percent from a
year earlier to 548.4 million ringgit ($182 million), according
to a company statement. The stock gained 0.2 percent to 5
ringgit.        Maxis Bhd. (MAXIS)  : Malaysia’s biggest mobile-phone
operator said first-quarter net income fell 2.4 percent from a
year earlier to 539 million ringgit, according to a company
statement. The stock was unchanged at 5.42 ringgit.       MMC Corp. (MMC MK): The construction, power and port
operator’s first-quarter profit rose 30 percent from a year
earlier to 43 million ringgit, according to a stock exchange
filing. The shares fell 0.7 percent to 2.79 ringgit.     Sunway Holdings Bhd. (SGW)  : The Malaysian construction
and property group’s first-quarter profit rose 8.4 percent from
a year earlier to 43.2 million ringgit as sales climbed,
according to a company statement. The stock gained 2.4 percent
to 2.57 ringgit.        Xidelang Holdings Ltd. (XIDE)  : The Chinese maker of
footwear products said first-quarter net income rose 3.4 percent
from a year earlier to 18.4 million ringgit, according to a
company statement. The shares were unchanged at 40.5 sen.  Zelan Bhd. (ZELN)  : The builder signed a preliminary
agreement with Tradewinds Corp. (TWC MK) to jointly submit a
tender for a hospital development project, according to a stock
exchange filing. Zelan fell 2.5 percent to 39 sen. Tradewinds
gained 2.1 percent to 96 sen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chan Tien Hin in  Kuala Lumpur  at 
